{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01ByEwNeTnxgCADBeSifZVPL","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! The current StatefulSet is the OLD one from the prior stages - it doesn't have:\n- The initContainer (`cert-selector`)\n- The transport cert volumes (ca1, ca2, transport-cert, transport-ca)\n- The ELASTIC_PASSWORD env var\n\nThe current cluster was inherited from the previous stages (seed-hosts-repair or internal-http-service-drift). It's running with the old config WITHOUT transport TLS enabled.\n\nNow I need to understand what this case is actually asking me to do:\n\n1. The case is `transport-additional-ca-trust`\n2. The scenario should be: A 3-node cluster with transport TLS configured, where es-cluster-2 uses a different CA than es-cluster-0 and es-cluster-1\n3. BUT the current cluster doesn't have transport TLS set up at all\n\nThe oracle checks:\n1. `es-transport-ca-bundle` configmap with at least 2 certs - CREATED by precondition fixture ✓\n2. Cluster health green with 3 nodes - currently green with 3 nodes ✓\n\nWait, but the oracle also checks that the `es-transport-ca-bundle` configmap has 2 certs. The fixture created it with 2 CA certs. Let me verify what the fixture actually set up.\n\nThe precondition flow is clear: the `es_env_ready` probe found running pods so it skipped any destructive rebuild, then `transport_ca_bundle_fixture` didn't find the configmap and created it with 2 CAs. Now the oracle will verify the configmap has 2 certs and the cluster is healthy with 3 nodes, both of which should pass. But the prompt mentions the cluster is degraded... I'm looking at how the oracle determines expected nodes by querying the live nodes and summing up the replicas from their backing StatefulSets. With the current cluster state of 3 nodes from the es-cluster StatefulSet, the expected count matches the actual count, so the oracle should pass. But the task description mentions a degraded cluster, so I need to trace back through the inherited state from the previous stage to understand what's actually happening. The oracle should pass since the cluster has 3 nodes running as expected and the configmap has the required 2 certificates. Since the `es_env_ready` probe already passed (exit code 0), the precondition's apply was skipped because the environment was already in the correct state, so no additional setup was needed.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1920,"cache_read_input_tokens":42589,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1920},"output_tokens":26,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"46e94186-2e7c-4845-a9f5-34d778fa0b31","uuid":"0efbef54-fa4a-40ea-9024-c9c7259fc5ea","request_id":"req_011CcQBPjHnt6wRpqiZcxgbS"}
