ne.\n\n---\n\n**What was found and what the script does:**\n\n| Setting | Current value | ES default | Revert method |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `audit-index` `number_of_shards` | `3` | `1` | **Static** — snapshot → delete → recreate → restore |\n| `audit-index` `routing.allocation.require.tier` | `hot` | unset | API: `PUT /audit-index/_settings` → `null` |\n| `audit-index` `routing.allocation.include._tier_preference` | `data_content` | unset | API: `PUT /audit-index/_settings` → `null` |\n| `node.attr.tier` (all 3 nodes) | `hot` | unset | **StatefulSet change** + rolling restart |\n| Cluster persistent/transient settings | both empty `{}` | empty | Nothing to revert |\n\n**ConfigMap `rollback-rehearsal`** is created in the `elasticsearch` namespace with a 7 KB `rollback.sh` that:\n1. Verifies cluster reachability before touching anything\n2. Clears both dynamic routing settings on `audit-index` via the settings API\n3. Emits clear `[WARN]` blocks with step-by-step instructions for the two out-of-band operations (shard-count reindex, StatefulSet rolling restart) that can't be done via API\n4. Exits non-zero if any API call fails=== /mydata/karma/runs/examples-rererun/mongodb-mongod-config-update-20260623_135802/stages/stage_1/submit.txt ===\nAll changes are applied and verified. Here's a summary:\n\n| Setting | Before | After |\n|---|---|---|\n| `systemLog.verbosity` | `1` | `2` |\n| `operationProfiling.slowOpThresholdMs` | `200` | `400` |\n| `wiredTiger.journalCompressor` | `zlib` | `zlib` (already correct) |\n\nAll three replica members report the new values (`logLevel: 2`, `slowOpThresholdMs: 400`). The rolling restart was done in safe order — secondaries first, then a `rs.stepDown()` before restarting the primary — so quorum was maintained throughout and data remained available.=== /mydata/karma/runs/examples-rererun/mongodb-tls-setup-20260623_141604/stages/stage_1/submit.txt ===\nTLS is fully enabled. Here's what was done:\n\n**Certificates generated** (openssl-toolbox → `mongo-tls` Secret):\n- `ca.crt` — self-signed CA certificate\n- `server.pem` — server cert (SANs for all 3 pod FQDNs + headless service) + key, concatenated\n- `client.pem` — client cert + key, concatenated\n\n**StatefulSet patched** to:\n- Mount `mongo-tls` Secret at `/etc/tls` (read-only)\n- Add `--tlsMode requireTLS --tlsCertificateKeyFile /etc/tls/server.pem --tlsCAFile /etc/tls/ca.crt` to `mongod`\n\n**Verification results:**\n- Plain connection → `MongoServerSelectionError: connection closed` (fails as required)\n- TLS connection with `/etc/tls/client.pem` + `/etc/tls/ca.crt` → `{ ok: 1 }` (succeeds)\n- Replica set healthy: 1 PRIMARY + 2 SECONDARY, all members communicating over TLS","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"46e94186-2e7c-4845-a9f5-34d778fa0b31","uuid":"d1a2710b-c46f-401a-ba5e-716e3b14b6e5","timestamp":"2026-06-25T15:03:14.807Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"=== /mydata/karma/runs/examples-rererun/spark-spark_streaming_autoscale-20260623_123516/stages/stage_1/submit.txt ===\nAll tasks completed successfully. Here's a summary:\n\n**Scaling events performed:**\n| Phase | Trigger | Action | Result |\n|-------|---------|--------|--------|\n| Phase 1 | LAG=2000, LATENCY=50ms | No action (5 workers sufficient) | 5 workers |\n| Phase 2 | LAG=15000, LATENCY=400ms | Scale up | 10 workers |\n| Phase 3 | LAG=75000, LATENCY=2500ms | Scale up | 20 workers |\n| Phase 4 | LAG=1500, LATENCY=45ms | Scale down | 5 workers |\n\n**Oracle success criteria met:**\n- Spark master + workers running\n- **3 scaling events** logged by metrics-server (`5→10`, `10→20`, `20→5`) — exceeds the 2-event minimum\n- Traffic generator completed all 4 phases and is still running=== /mydata/karma/runs/examples-rererun/ray-deploy_cluster-20260623_115423/stages/stage_1/submit.txt ===\nEverything is in order. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**Deployed:**\n- `ray-head` Deployment (1 replica) — already had `--num-cpus=0` so it doesn't take tasks\n- `ray-h